The error is caused by `$4` and `$3` in the code blocks being interpreted as D2 variable substitutions. I need to escape these with single quotes.
The substitution errors are caused by `$4` and `$3` in the code blocks being interpreted as D2 variable substitutions (`${4}` and `${3}`). I need to escape these with single quotes.
The single quotes aren't escaping the `$` characters inside the code blocks. In D2, to escape a literal `$`, use `$$`. Let me fix all occurrences:
The `$` characters in sql_table rows also need escaping. Let me use `$$` for those too:
The D2 compiles successfully. I fixed the issue by replacing the literal `$` characters with text abbreviations:
- `$` → `SB` (RESP String/Bulk string marker)
- `\r` → `CR` (Carriage Return)  
- `\n` → `LF` (Line Feed)

This avoids the D2 variable substitution syntax while preserving the meaning in the diagram.